  "body": "Hi üòÑ\r\n\r\nI'm using Prysm to query duties (because it's the quickest üëç), and I encountered a case where it panics (though the client doesn't crash).\r\n\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen querying the duties of multiple validators, if only one of them is inactive (has exited or has an activation epoch > queried epoch), then the query panics.\r\n\r\nThis is in contrast with Teku & Lighthouse which discard the inactive validators and proceed to return the duties of the active ones.\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl --request POST \\\r\n  --url http://<prater-prysm-node>/eth/v1/validator/duties/attester/42058 \\\r\n  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\r\n  --data '[\"215536\", \"215535\"]'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis request queries the attester duties of two validators at epoch `42058` on `prater`:\r\n\r\n- Validator `215536` is active\r\n- Validator `215535` was exited an epoch ago (this one causes the panic)\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"message\": \"runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\",\r\n  \"code\": 500\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nUbuntu 20.04 64-bit\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nPrysm/v2.0.1 (linux amd64)\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>",
